snippet.textDisplay: Y’all... come on now I love nicki and have been idolizing her since I was In second grade but this isn’t the best she can do this is very weak compared to her past work. Pink Friday all the way up to Queen were absolutely beautiful albums with a lot of work put into them but I think we can all agree Nicki is best when she’s RAW when she’s aggressive but not cocky and when she hits that little sentimental spot like how we saw in The Pinkprint. Now it’s all about numbers and being the best for her. That’s all I hear her talking about in her music now... how she’s the best and will always be. It’s not what rap is and she even knows it. It comes from YOU and your experiences and what inspires you even not about rapping about being better than everyone else. I love her but I can say on behalf on me and other barbs I’ve spoken to that we are disappointed and hope she pulls it together with this last album.
